Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from the fridge to allow them to come to room temperature.

Halve the @Salad Potatoes{350} widthways. Put the potatoes onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf, ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add half the @Balsamic Glaze{24} and half the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40} into a #large bowl{} with the @Olive Oil{1} and @Water{3} for the dressing.

Mix together and season with salt and pepper, then set the dressing aside.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125} and pop them onto a piece of #foil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the garlic, the remaining balsamic glaze and the @Butter{20} to the foil. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a #small baking tray{}.

Season the steaks with salt and pepper on both sides. Set aside.

Pop the tomatoes to roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven. Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or #pot{} to lightly crush each potato half.

Sprinkle over the remaining Parmigiano Reggiano and drizzle the potatoes with more oil. Return to the top shelf until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

When the potatoes have ~{10%minutes} left, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

> Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and medium-rare, about ~{1%minute} ~{15%seconds} on each side.

> Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with foil and allow to rest for a couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw steaks. They're safe to eat when browned on the outside.

Just before everything's ready toss the @Wild Rocket{40} in the Parmigiano dressing.

Thinly slice the steaks widthways, then share the steak, Parmigiano smashed potatoes and rocket salad between your plates.

Gently mix the tomato mixture within the foil, then spoon the slow roasted tomatoes and butter sauce over the steaks to finish.

Enjoy!